      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cleaning Up The Mideast</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Israel Policy Forum pres Seymour D Reich letter holds that Pres Bush must use his remaining time in office to take charge and bring order to Middle East</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''What a Mess'' (column, June 6), Thomas L. Friedman quotes from Dr. Seuss' ''Cat in the Hat'' to sum up today's Middle East: ''This mess is so big'' that ''we can not pick it up.'' But in the end, the Cat in the Hat comes through and cleans up the mess.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''What a Mess'' (column, June 6), Thomas L. Friedman quotes from Dr. Seuss' ''Cat in the Hat'' to sum up today's Middle East: ''This mess is so big'' that ''we can not pick it up.'' But in the end, the Cat in the Hat comes through and cleans up the mess.</p>
        <p>The Israeli-Palestinian conflict grows messier each month. According to polls last month, 62 percent of Palestinians support a truce with Israel and 47 percent of Israeli Jews even support direct negotiations with Hamas to stop rocket fire.</p>
        <p>The only one capable of cleaning up the mess is the president of the United States. President Bush must use his remaining time in office to take charge and bring order and hope to this messy region.</p>
        <p>Seymour D. Reich  President, Israel Policy Forum  New York, June 6, 2007</p>
      </block>
